1 AMEND House Bill No. 2885, Page 4, Section 306.030, Line 98, by inserting after all of said
2 section and line the following:
3
4 "306.127. 1. Beginning January 1, 2005, every person born after January 1, 1984 and
5 before January 1, 2006, or as required pursuant to section 306.128, who operates a vessel on the
6 lakes of this state shall possess, on the vessel, a boating safety identification card issued by the
7 water patrol division or its agent which shows that he or she has:
8 (1) Successfully completed a boating safety course approved by the National Association
9 of State Boating Law Administrators and certified by the water patrol division. The boating
10 safety course may include a course sponsored by the United States Coast Guard Auxiliary or the
11 United States Power Squadron. The water patrol division may appoint agents to administer a
12 boater education course or course equivalency examination and issue boater identification cards
13 under guidelines established by the water patrol. The water patrol division shall maintain a list
14 of approved courses; or
15 (2) Successfully passed an equivalency examination prepared by the water patrol
16 division and administered by the water patrol division or its agent. The equivalency examination
17 shall have a degree of difficulty equal to, or greater than, that of the examinations given at the
18 conclusion of an approved boating safety course; or
19 (3) A valid master's, mate's, or operator's license issued by the United States Coast
20 Guard.
21 2. Beginning January 1, 2027, every person born on or after January 1, 2006, or as
22 required pursuant to section 306.128, who operates a vessel on the waters of this state shall
23 possess, on the vessel, a boating safety identification card issued by the water patrol division or
24 its agent which shows that he or she has:
25 (1) Successfully completed a boating safety course approved by the National Association
26 of State Boating Law Administrators and certified by the water patrol division. The boating
27 safety course may include a course sponsored by the United States Coast Guard Auxiliary or the
28 United States Power Squadron. The water patrol division may appoint agents to administer a
29 boater education course or course equivalency examination and issue boater identification cards
