1 under guidelines established by the water patrol. The water patrol division shall maintain a list
2 of approved courses; or
3 (2) Successfully passed an equivalency examination prepared by the water patrol
4 division and administered by the water patrol division or its agent. The equivalency examination
5 shall have a degree of difficulty equal to, or greater than, that of the examinations given at the
6 conclusion of an approved boating safety course; or
7 (3) A valid master's, mate's, or operator's license issued by the United States Coast
8 Guard.
9 3. The water patrol division or its agent shall issue a permanent boating safety
10 identification card to each person who complies with the requirements of this section which is
11 valid for life unless invalidated pursuant to law.
12 [3.] 4. The water patrol division may charge a fee for such card or any replacement card
13 that does not substantially exceed the costs of administrating this section. The water patrol
14 division or its designated agent shall collect such fees. These funds shall be forwarded to
15 general revenue.
16 [4.] 5. The provisions of this section shall not apply to any person who:
17 (1) Is licensed by the United States Coast Guard to serve as master of a vessel;
18 (2) Operates a vessel only on a private lake or pond that is not classified as waters of the
19 state;
20 (3) Until January 1, 2006, is a nonresident who is visiting the state for sixty days or less;
21 (4) Is participating in an event or regatta approved by the water patrol;
22 (5) Is a nonresident who has proof of a valid boating certificate or license issued by
23 another state if the boating course is approved by the National Association of State Boating Law
24 Administrators (NASBLA);
25 (6) Is exempted by rule of the water patrol;
26 (7) Is currently serving in any branch of the United States Armed Forces, reserves, or
27 Missouri National Guard, or any spouse of a person currently in such service; or
28 (8) Has previously successfully completed a boating safety education course approved
29 by the National Association of State Boating Law Administrators (NASBLA).
30 [5.] 6. The water patrol division shall inform other states of the requirements of this
31 section.
32 [6.] 7. No individual shall be detained or stopped strictly for the purpose of checking
33 whether the individual possesses a boating safety identification card or a temporary boater
34 education permit.
35 [7.] 8. Any person or company that rents or sells vessels may issue a temporary boating
36 safety identification card to an individual to operate a rented vessel or a vessel being considered
37 for sale, for a period of up to seven days, provided that the individual meets the minimum age
38 requirements for operating a vessel in this state. In order to qualify for the temporary boating
Page 2 of 3

6206H02.04H
1 safety identification card, the applicant shall provide a valid driver's license and shall sign an
2 affidavit that he or she has reviewed the Missouri state highway patrol handbook of Missouri
3 boating laws and responsibilities. Any individual holding a valid temporary boating safety
4 identification card shall be deemed in compliance with the requirements of this section. The
5 Missouri state highway patrol shall charge a fee of nine dollars for such temporary boating safety
6 identification card. Individuals shall not be eligible for more than one temporary boating safety
7 identification card. No person or company may issue a temporary boating safety identification
8 card to an individual under the provisions of this subsection unless such person or company is
9 capable of submitting the applicant's temporary boating safety identification card information
10 and payment in an electronic format as prescribed by the Missouri state highway patrol. The
11 business entity issuing a temporary boating safety identification card to an individual under the
12 provisions of this subsection shall transmit the applicant's temporary boating safety identification
13 card information electronically to the Missouri state highway patrol, in a manner and format
14 prescribed by the superintendent, using an electronic online registration process developed and
15 provided by the Missouri state highway patrol. The electronic online process developed and
16 provided by the Missouri state highway patrol shall allow the applicant to pay the temporary
17 boating safety identification card fee by credit card or debit card. Notwithstanding any provision
18 in section 306.185 to the contrary, all fees collected under the authority of this subsection shall
19 be deposited in the water patrol division fund. The Missouri state highway patrol shall
20 promulgate rules for developing the temporary boating safety identification card and any
21 requirements necessary to the issuance, processing, and payment of the temporary boating safety
22 identification card. The Missouri state highway patrol shall, by rule, develop a boating safety
23 checklist for each applicant seeking a temporary boating safety identification card. Nothing in
24 this subsection shall allow a holder of a temporary boating safety identification card to receive a
25 notation on the person's driver's license or nondriver identification under section 302.184. The
26 provisions of this subsection shall expire on December 31, 2032."; and
27
28 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
29 accordingly.
